    "title": "Resolve pre-merge build-gate ownership: DDx implementation or CONTRACT-001 amendment",
    "description": "CONTRACT-001 'Post-Cycle HELIX Behavior' table asserts DDx owns 'Build gate (pre-merge check)'. Verified on 2026-04-17 that no implementation exists: grep of ddx/cli/internal/agent/*.go for lefthook|cargo check|build-health|BuildGate returns nothing. HELIX today runs cargo check / lefthook run pre-commit post-agent-commit and git reverts on failure (scripts/helix:3629-3654).\n\nTwo possible resolutions, chosen by the contract audit (helix-00e2486f):\n\nOption A — DDx implementation: file a new bead in DDx's own tracker for a pre-land build-gate hook (lefthook / cargo check / repo-declared gate script) that runs before fast-forward merge and aborts the attempt with a preserved ref on failure. HELIX keeps its current gate as a belt-and-suspenders guard until DDx ships.\n\nOption B — CONTRACT-001 amendment: amend the Post-Cycle HELIX Behavior table to move 'Build gate (pre-merge check)' from DDx-owned to HELIX-owned. Keep HELIX's existing implementation; document it in CONTRACT-001 as HELIX's responsibility.\n\nThis bead is absorbed if helix-00e2486f's audit resolves it. Otherwise, whichever option is chosen must produce a code change that makes the contract claim true.",
    "acceptance": "Either (a) a new DDx-side bead is filed in DDx's tracker with deterministic acceptance for a pre-land build-gate and CONTRACT-001 links to it, OR (b) docs/helix/02-design/contracts/CONTRACT-001-ddx-helix-boundary.md is amended to move 'Build gate (pre-merge check)' from DDx-owned to HELIX-owned in the Post-Cycle table and the contract-audit matrix (helix-00e2486f output) reflects the amendment. Bead closes only when the contract and implementation no longer disagree.",
